<paragraph id="87183694910E595FAC1ADCDB215DFCD5" blockId="5.[792,1419,346,883]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<taxonomicName id="40A74D17910E595FAC1ADCDB26B9FE15" baseAuthorityName="Lucas" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[831,1022,410,435]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Butocrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insignis">
<emphasis id="B5D3EA86910E595FAC1ADCDB26B9FE15" box="[831,1022,410,435]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Butocrysa insignis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<materialsCitation id="37CF3CC9910E595FAB27DCDB2119FD95" collectorName="However" country="Brazil" location="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="holotype">
was described from“Brésil intérieur” [inland 
<collectingCountry id="FFB07604910E595FAC4ADCFB26F7FE75" box="[879,944,442,467]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Brazil</collectingCountry>
], as 
<emphasis id="B5D3EA86910E595FACC6DCFB219FFE75" box="[995,1240,442,467]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<taxonomicName id="40A74D17910E595FACC6DCFB2193FE75" authorityName="Lucas" authorityYear="1859" box="[995,1236,442,467]" genus="Amphionycha" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" rank="species" species="insignis">Amphionycha insignis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
It has been reported that the species was described based on a single specimen (
<typeStatus id="581C8836910E595FACB3DCBB26B8FDB5" box="[918,1023,506,531]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">holotype</typeStatus>
). 
<collectorName id="2A525342910E595FAB36DCBB213FFDB5" box="[1043,1144,506,531]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">However</collectorName>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="E3364B65910E595FABA1DCBB2055FDB5" author="Lucas, P. H." box="[1156,1298,506,531]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refId="ref15545" refString="Lucas, P. H. 1857. Entomologie. In: Animaux nouveaux ou rares recueillis pendant l'expedition dans les parties centrales de l'Amerique du Sud, de Rio de Janeiro a Lima, et de Lima au Para, executee par ordre du Gouvernement Francais pendant les annees 1843 a 1847, sous la direction du Comte F. de Castelnau. Paris, Bertrand. 204 p." type="book" year="1857">Lucas (1857)</bibRefCitation>
indicated: “ 
<taxonomicName id="40A74D17910E595FAC06DF5B2169FD95" authority="INSIGNIS" authorityName="INSIGNIS" box="[803,1070,538,563]" genus="Amphionycha" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B5D3EA86910E595FAC06DF5B2169FD95" box="[803,1070,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">AMPHIONYCHA INSIGNIS</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(2)”
</materialsCitation>
; 
<materialsCitation id="37CF3CC9910E595FAB43DF5B2151FCD5" collectionCode="BMNH" collectorName="M. Le Comte de Castelnau" country="Brazil" county="Dej. Cat. des Coleopt." location="Le Comte de Castelnau" municipality="Scientific Commission of South" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Minas Gerais" typeStatus="syntype">
“(2) 
<collectingCounty id="6E794E18910E595FABB1DF5B20C0FD95" box="[1172,1415,538,563]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Dej. Cat. des Coléopt.</collectingCounty>
, 3 
<superScript id="70D29BDC910E595FAC02DF782668FDEE" attach="left" box="[807,815,569,584]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">e</superScript>
edit., p. 379”. Accordingly, the specimens from Pierre François Marie Auguste Dejean (currently in the 
<collectionCode id="E1B6AE51910E595FAA1EDF1B20C3FDD5" box="[1339,1412,602,627]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">BMNH</collectionCode>
) are 
<typeStatus id="581C8836910E595FAC6FDF3B26E8FD35" box="[842,943,634,659]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">syntypes</typeStatus>
. Apparently, Dejean was involved in the identification of the specimens because Lucas himself indicated this (translated): “By doing so, I hope to signal sufficiently the entomological riches gathered by the 
<collectingMunicipality id="677CACEE910E595FAC3FDFBB2133FCB5" box="[794,1140,762,787]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Scientific Commission of South</collectingMunicipality>
<taxonomicName id="40A74D17910E595FAB5FDFBB219FFCB5" box="[1146,1240,762,787]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="America" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">America</taxonomicName>
, under the skillful direction of 
<collectorName id="2A525342910E595FACEFDE5B21B3FC95" box="[970,1268,794,819]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
M. 
<location id="8278604F910E595FACC8DE5B21B3FC95" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:0F0E8782910E595FACBCDDBB215DFCD5:8278604F910E595FACC8DE5B21B3FC95" box="[1005,1268,794,819]" country="Brazil" county="Dej. Cat. des Coleopt." municipality="Scientific Commission of South" name="Le Comte de Castelnau" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" stateProvince="Minas Gerais">Le Comte de Castelnau</location>
</collectorName>
”. Currently, it is known from 
<collectingCountry id="FFB07604910E595FACE2DE7B2144FCF5" box="[967,1027,826,851]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="4563F876910E595FAB34DE7B21E1FCF5" box="[1041,1190,826,851]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="4563F876910E595FAB94DE7B2012FCF5" box="[1201,1365,826,851]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="4563F876910E595FAA44DE7B261DFCD5" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="E3364B65910E595FAC4EDE1B2157FCD5" author="Monne, M. A." box="[875,1040,858,883]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refId="ref16366" refString="Monne, M. A. 2020 b. Catalogue of the Cerambycidae (Coleoptera) of the Neotropical region. Part II. Subfamily Lamiinae. Available at: https: // cerambycids. com / catalog. Access in: 04 / 2020." type="url" year="2020">Monné, 2020b</bibRefCitation>
)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
